<title>BRAZIL: Brazil bolsas halt trade in CVRD.</title>
<headline>Brazil bolsas halt trade in CVRD.</headline>
<dateline>SAO PAULO 1997-03-05</dateline>
<text>
<p>Brazilian stock exchanges said they have suspended trade in state mining giant Companhia Vale do Rio Doce (CVRD).</p>
<p>Trade was halted following a request from Brazil's Securities and Exchange Commission (CVM), a spokeswoman for Sao Paulo Stock Exchange (Bovespa) said.  </p>
<p>The CVM gave no further details, she added.</p>
<p>Brazil's National Privatization Council (CND) was meeting this morning to discuss the tender documents for Vale's sale.</p>
<p>((-- Fatima Cristina, Sao Paulo Newsroom 5511 2485412))</p>
